spirit:component.spirit:name: axi_timer_0

spirit:field.spirit:name: MDT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer 0 Mode 0 - Timer mode is generate 1 - Timer mode is capture

spirit:field.spirit:name: UDT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Up/Down Count Timer 0 0 - Timer functions as up counter 1 - Timer functions as down counter

spirit:field.spirit:name: GENT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable External Generate Signal Timer 0 0 - Disables external generate signal 1 - Enables external generate signal

spirit:field.spirit:name: CAPT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable External Capture Trigger Timer 0 0 - Disables external capture trigger 1 - Enables external capture trigger

spirit:field.spirit:name: ARHT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Auto Reload/Hold Timer 0. When the timer is in Generate mode, this bit determines whether the counter reloads the generate value and continues running or holds at the termination value. In Capture mode, this bit determines whether a new capture trigger overwrites the previous captured value or if the previous value is held. 0 = Hold counter or capture value. The TLR must be read before providing the external capture. 1 = Reload generate value or overwrite capture value

spirit:field.spirit:name: LOAD0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Load Timer 0 0 = No load 1 = Loads timer with value in TLR0 Setting this bit loads timer/counter register (TCR0) with a specified value in the timer/counter load register (TLR0). This bit prevents the running of the timer/counter; hence, this should be cleared alongside setting Enable Timer/ Counter (ENT0) bit in TCSR0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ENIT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable Interrupt for Timer 0 Enables the assertion of the interrupt signal for this timer. Has no effect on the interrupt flag (T0INT) in TCSR0. 0 - Disable interrupt signal 1 - Enable interrupt signal

spirit:field.spirit:name: ENT0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable Timer 0 0 - Disable timer (counter halts) 1 - Enable timer (counter runs)

spirit:field.spirit:name: T0INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer 0 Interrupt Indicates that the condition for an interrupt on this timer has occurred. If the timer mode is capture and the timer is enabled, this bit indicates a capture has occurred. If the mode is generate, this bit indicates the counter has rolled over. Must be cleared by writing a 1. Read: 0 - No interrupt has occurred 1 - Interrupt has occurred Write: 0 - No change in state of T0INT 1 - Clear T0INT (clear to 0)

spirit:field.spirit:name: PWMA0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable Pulse Width Modulation for Timer 0 0 - Disable pulse width modulation 1 - Enable pulse width modulation PWM requires using Timer 0 and Timer 1 together as a pair. Timer 0 sets the period of the PWM output, and Timer 1 sets the high time for the PWM output. For PWM mode, MDT0 and MDT1 must be 0 and C_GEN0_ASSERT and C_GEN1_ASSERT must be 1.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ENALL
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable All Timers 0 - No effect on timers 1 - Enable all timers (counters run) This bit is mirrored in all control/status registers and is used to enable all counters simultaneously. Writing a 1 to this bit sets ENALL, ENT0, and ENT1. Writing a 0 to this register clears ENALL but has no effect on ENT0 and ENT1.

spirit:field.spirit:name: CASC
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable cascade mode of timers 0 - Disable cascaded operation 1 - Enable cascaded operation Cascaded operation requires using Timer 0 and Timer 1 together as a pair. The counting event for the Timer 1 is when the Timer 0 rolls over from all 1s to all 0s or vice-versa when counting down. TLR0 and TLR1 are used for lower 32-bit and higher 32-bit respectively. Similarly, TCR0 contains lower 32-bits for the 64-bit counter and TCR1 contains the higher 32-bits. Only TCSR0 is valid for both the timer/counters in this mode. This CASC bit must be set before enabling the timer/counter.

spirit:field.spirit:name: TCLR0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer/Counter Load Register

spirit:field.spirit:name: TCR0
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer/Counter Register

spirit:field.spirit:name: MDT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer 1 Mode 0 - Timer mode is generate 1 - Timer mode is capture

spirit:field.spirit:name: UDT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Up/Down Count Timer 1 0 - Timer functions as up counter 1 - Timer functions as down counter

spirit:field.spirit:name: GENT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable External Generate Signal Timer 1 0 - Disables external generate signal 1 - Enables external generate signal

spirit:field.spirit:name: CAPT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable External Capture Trigger Timer 1 0 - Disables external capture trigger 1 - Enables external capture trigger

spirit:field.spirit:name: ARHT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Auto Reload/Hold Timer 1. When the timer is in Generate mode, this bit determines whether the counter reloads the generate value and continues running or holds at the termination value. In Capture mode, this bit determines whether a new capture trigger overwrites the previous captured value or if the previous value is held. 0 = Hold counter or capture value. The TLR must be read before providing the external capture. 1 = Reload generate value or overwrite capture value

spirit:field.spirit:name: LOAD1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Load Timer 1 0 = No load 1 = Loads timer with value in TLR1 Setting this bit loads timer/counter register (TCR1) with a specified value in the timer/counter load register (TLR1). This bit prevents the running of the timer/counter; hence, this should be cleared alongside setting Enable Timer/ Counter (ENT1) bit in TCSR1.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ENIT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable Interrupt for Timer 1 Enables the assertion of the interrupt signal for this timer. Has no effect on the interrupt flag (T1INT) in TCSR1. 0 - Disable interrupt signal 1 - Enable interrupt signal

spirit:field.spirit:name: ENT1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable Timer 1 0 - Disable timer (counter halts) 1 - Enable timer (counter runs)

spirit:field.spirit:name: T1INT
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer 1 Interrupt Indicates that the condition for an interrupt on this timer has occurred. If the timer mode is capture and the timer is enabled, this bit indicates a capture has occurred. If the mode is generate, this bit indicates the counter has rolled over. Must be cleared by writing a 1. Read: 0 - No interrupt has occurred 1 - Interrupt has occurred Write: 0 - No change in state of T0INT 1 - Clear T1INT (clear to 0)

spirit:field.spirit:name: PWMA1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable Pulse Width Modulation for Timer 1 0 - Disable pulse width modulation 1 - Enable pulse width modulation PWM requires using Timer 0 and Timer 1 together as a pair. Timer 0 sets the period of the PWM output, and Timer 1 sets the high time for the PWM output. For PWM mode, MDT0 and MDT1 must be 0.

spirit:field.spirit:name: ENALL
spirit:field.spirit:description: Enable All Timers 0 - No effect on timers 1 - Enable all timers (counters run) This bit is mirrored in all control/status registers and is used to enable all counters simultaneously. Writing a 1 to this bit sets ENALL, ENT0, and ENT1. Writing a 0 to this register clears ENALL but has no effect on ENT0 and ENT1.

spirit:field.spirit:name: TCLR1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer/Counter Load Register

spirit:field.spirit:name: TCR1
spirit:field.spirit:description: Timer/Counter Register

spirit:component.spirit:description: The AXI Timer/Counter is a 32/64-bit timer module that attaches to the AXI4-Lite interface

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TRIG0_ASSERT
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Assertion level for capture trigger0. It can be active high or active low

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: TRIG1_ASSERT
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Assertion level for capture trigger1. It can be active high or active low

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: GEN0_ASSERT
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Active state of Generate Out signal
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Assertion level for generateout0. It can be active high or active low

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: GEN1_ASSERT
spirit:parameter.spirit:displayName: Active state of Generate Out signal
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Assertion level for generateout1. It can be active high or active low

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: COUNT_WIDTH
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Width of timer can be selected from the range of 8 to 32

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: mode_64bit
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: This is cascaded mode. The two timer are cascaded to operate as a single 64 bit counter
